Remaking my most requested recipe, Copycat Sweetgreen Harvest Bowl. This is my go-to salad at Sweetgreen and the easiest meal to make at home if you can’t get to a location. It’s THE BEST! 

Serves: 4 
Ingredients:
8 cups kale, chopped
1 apple, cut into small pieces
1/2 cup roasted almonds, chopped small
1 small sweet potato, peeled and chopped into small pieces and roasted 
1/2 cup feta or goats cheese 

Dressing:
1 heaped teaspoon Dijon mustard
1 teaspoon honey 
1/4 cup balsamic vinegar
5 tablespoons olive oil 
1/4 teaspoon salt 
1/8 teaspoon pepper 

Method:
1. In a small bowl, mix all the dressing ingredients. 
2. Combine all salad ingredients in a large bowl. Pour dressing over the salad, toss, and enjoy!

Add roasted chicken to the salad for extra protein. And the apple can be taken out if you aren’t a fan of fruit it salads. 

💚💚

Fresh Caprese Salad, my most requested recipe to date. This Salad hits all the right notes. It’s full of delicious ingredients like mozzarella and fresh basil, and is a side dish you can whip up in no time. It’s my summer favorite! 

Ingredients:
3 cups Cherry Tomatoes, halved 
1 heirloom tomato, sliced (optional)
1 cup mozzarella balls, halved 
1 cup fresh basil leaves 
1/2 teaspoon salt 
1/4 teaspoon pepper 
4 tablespoons olive oil
3 tablespoons balsamic vinegar 

Method:
1. Place the halved cherry tomatoes, sliced heirloom tomato, mozzarella balls, and torn fresh basil leaves into a large serving bowl or plate. 
2. Mix the olive oil and balsamic vinegar together and drizzle over the ingredients, and sprinkle the salt and pepper over evenly. 
3. For the best flavor, let rest for 15-30 minutes so the flavors can combine well. 

Enjoy ❤️

Chicken Katsu Bowl with spicy creamy Mayo, crispy chicken and fresh greens make an incredibly comforting dish. This is an easy recipe to make at home and the taste is *chefs kiss*. 

Ingredients:
1x chicken breast, sliced horizontally 
1/3 cup rice
1 spring (green) onion, sliced 
1/3 cup soy sauce or tamari 
1 tablespoon honey 
1 tablespoon sesame oil
1 teaspoon grated ginger 
1 ginger clove, minced
2 tablespoons sesame seeds 
3/4 cup panko breadcrumbs 
Olive oil 
Sauce: 
1/4 cup mayonnaise 
1 tablespoon sriracha
1 teaspoon soy sauce or tamari 

Method:
In a bowl, combine soy sauce, honey, sesame oil, ginger, garlic and spring  onion. Add chicken and marinate in bowl for at least 20 minutes. Ensure chicken is covered well in marinade. 
While the chicken is marinating, cook rice and prepare Mayo. Add mayonnaise, sriracha and soy sauce to a small bowl and mix well. 
On a large plate, add sesame seeds and bread crumbs, combine. Cover chicken in the breadcrumb mix and push the mix into the chicken so it sticks well. 
Heat a large skillet or pan over medium heat and add olive oil. Cook chicken for 3 minutes on each side or until crispy. Remove and cut into slices. 
Add rice and chicken to a serving bowl and add vegetables of choice, drizzle with Sriracha Mayo. 

Enjoy x 

#chickenkatsu #recipe #dinner

Strawberry & Yogurt Collagen Bites 🍓 These viral Bites are my newest obsession! Creamy Greek Yogurt with fresh strawberries, vanilla collagen, topped with milk chocolate and finished with a sprinkling of sea salt. An irresistible and healthier alternative to ice cream. Keep in the freezer for a delicious snack. 

Ingredients:
2 servings @doseandco Collagen Creamer (can be swapped for any Dose & Co Collagen)
2 cups strawberries, diced - can also use other fruit 
1 cup plain Greek yogurt
1 cup chocolate chips
 
Method:
1. In a bowl, combine yogurt, strawberries and collagen, mix well. Line a tray with baking paper.
2. Using a tablespoon, scoop the yogurt mixture onto the lined tray. Be sure to leave room between each yogurt bite. Place tray into the freezer for 1 hour.
3. Melt the chocolate in a bowl and remove frozen bites from the freezer.
4. Dip each bite into the chocolate and place back onto the lined tray. Place in refrigerator for 30 minutes before serving.

Enjoy ❤️

#frozenyogurt #yogurtbites #dessert #healthyrecipes

Feeling under the weather? This soothing Honey & Lemon Drink recipe is a refreshing and comforting drink that is perfect if you’re feeling run down or wanting something to sip on during a cool day. This homemade, delicious drink is made with 5 simple ingredients and is ready in 5 minutes. Perfect for adults and children. 
Ginger is a powerhouse of nutrients and has anti-inflammatory and anti-microbial properties to help relieve congestion and boost immunity. Honey not only contains antibacterial compounds but also immunomodulatory compounds which makes it an effective remedy to deal with common infections, soothe sore throats and boost immunity.
Lemon is a great source of vitamin C which is essential for fighting off colds, flus and to boost immunity. 

Serves: 2
Preparation: 5 minutes 
Ingredients:
2 lemons, sliced in half
2 tablespoons honey
2 mint leaves
1 teaspoon ginger, chopped finely
Boiling water

Method:
1. Add chopped ginger to 2 glasses.
2. Squeeze 3 lemon halves into the 2 glasses and top with boiling water.
3. Slice the remaining lemon half. Add honey and top glass with lemon slices and mint leaves. Mix well and serve warm.

Enjoy 💛

Quick, easy, and flavorful, this is one of my favorite weeknight meals to make (plus the kids love it too). Filled with bursts of juicy tomato goodness, garlic, parmesan, and basil, and can be whipped up in 25 minutes. Cherry tomatoes are now in season in New Zealand and available in supermarkets nationwide. These small, bite-sized tomatoes are a popular choice for salads, snacks, and various culinary creations. Not only do they add a burst of flavour to dishes, but they also offer an array of nutritional benefits being rich in vitamin C, potassium and beta-carotene.

Garlic Pasta with Cherry Tomatoes
Serves: 4
Preparation: 5 minutes      
Cooking: 20 minutes

Ingredients:
300 grams cherry tomatoes
220 grams spaghetti
3 garlic cloves, minced
¼ cup olive oil
¼ cup parmesan cheese
½ cup fresh basil
Pinch salt 
Pinch pepper

Method:
Being a large pot of salted water to boil. Cook spaghetti until al dente according to package directions. Once cooked, drain the water, and add a small amount of oil so the pasta doesn’t stick together. 
Heat a skillet over medium heat and add 1 tablespoon of oil. Add the cherry tomatoes and cook until soft, around 5-7 minutes. Add the garlic, pinch of salt and pepper and cook for 1 minute.
Using a spoon or potato masher, mash the tomatoes to release their juices. 
Cook for another 5 minutes until the tomatoes are very soft.
Place the cooked pasta on top of the tomato, as well as the basil and parmesan cheese. 
Serve immediately and add more basil or cheese if desired. 

Enjoy ❤️
